# Project-generated artifacts — large, regenerable
data/raw/
data/processed/
# Episode trajectories live under data/dataset_<seed>/runs/ and are NOT committed
# (covered by `runs/` + `*.npz` below). The dataset's metadata.json is committed
# on purpose — it fully describes the dataset and can regenerate it:
#   python scripts/generate_dataset.py --from-metadata data/dataset_<seed>/metadata.json
# Throwaway sweep / probe corpora from dev investigations. The `runs/` + `*.npz`
# rules already keep the bulk out, but each dir's metadata.json is not covered and
# would ride along on a careless `git add`. Named datasets (data/dataset_<n>/) keep
# their committed metadata.json on purpose — see the note above.
data/_*/
data/*_sweep/
data/*_sweep[0-9]/
data/*_probe/
data/dagger_*/

runs/
checkpoints/
logs/
outputs/
wandb/
mlruns/
*.npz
*.parquet
*.pt
*.pth
*.ckpt

